{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850043513,"sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","part":{"id":"prt_d78e9342c001dBrakWVyH5gKdQ","messageID":"msg_d78e9238c001JOUfQeSEqnYDyw","sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_be43e00872234b0481dbae03","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n208: \n209: ```python\n210: class DockerService:\n211:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n212:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n213:     def build_image(\n214:         self,\n215:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n216:         context_path: Path,\n217:         image_name: str,\n218:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n219:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n220:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n221:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n222:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n223:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n224:     def push_image(\n225:         self,\n226:         image_name: str,\n227:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n228:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n229:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n230:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n231:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n232:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n233:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: class MetadataService:\n240:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n241:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n242:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n243:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n244:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n245:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n246:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n250: \n251: ```python\n252: class KubernetesProvider:\n253:     def __init__(\n254:         self,\n255:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n256:         verbose: bool = False,\n257:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n258:     ) -> None: ...\n259:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n260:     def deploy_agent(\n261:         self,\n262:         agent_name: str,\n263:         image_url: str,\n264:         port: int,\n265:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n266:         replicas: int = 1,\n267:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n268:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n269:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n270:     def _create_deployment(\n271:         self,\n272:         name: str,\n273:         image_url: str,\n274:         port: int,\n275:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n276:         replicas: int,\n277:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n278:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n279:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n280:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n281:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n282:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n283:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n287: \n288: ```python\n289: class AgentCubeProvider:\n290:     def __init__(\n291:         self,\n292:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n293:         verbose: bool = False,\n294:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n295:     ) -> None: ...\n296:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n297:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n298:         self,\n299:         agent_name: str,\n300:         image_url: str,\n301:         port: int,\n302:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n303:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n304:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n306:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n307:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n308:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n309:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n310:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n311: ```\n312: \n313: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n314: \n315: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n316: \n317: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n318: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n319: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n320: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n321: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n322: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n323: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n324: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n325: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n326: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n327: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n328: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n329: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n330: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n331: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n332: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n333: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n334: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n335: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n336: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n337: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n338: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n339: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n340: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n341: \n342: Validators: `validate_language` → `['python','java']` lowercase; `validate_build_mode` → `['local','cloud']` lowercase; `validate_port` → `1..65535`.\n343: \n344: ## `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n345: \n346: Dataclass fields (all `Optional` unless noted):\n347: \n348: | Field | Type | Default |\n349: |-------|------|---------|\n350: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n351: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n352: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n353: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n354: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n355: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n356: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n357: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n358: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n359: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n360: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n361: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n362: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n363: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n364: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n365: \n366: ```python\n367: @classmethod\n368: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n372: \n373: **`[project]` dependencies:**\n374: \n375: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`\n376: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`\n377: - `pyyaml>=6.0`\n378: - `httpx>=0.24.0`\n379: - `docker>=6.0.0`\n380: - `rich>=13.0.0`\n381: - `packaging>=23.0`\n382: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0`\n383: - `semver>=3.0.0`\n384: \n385: **Optional `[project.optional-dependencies]`:**\n386: \n387: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n388: - `dev`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `ruff>=0.1.0`, `mypy>=1.5.0`, `pre-commit>=3.3.0`, `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n389: - `test`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`, `httpx-mock>=0.10.0`\n390: \n391: **Python:** `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`.\n392: \n393: ## Top-level exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n394: \n395: - `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n396: - `__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"`\n397: - `__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"`\n398: - Imports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n399: - `__all__` = `[\"app\", \"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\"]`  \n400:   (`StatusRuntime` is not exported here.)\n\n(End of file - total 400 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n\n## Package layout (every module path and role)\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775850043492,"end":1775850043510}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850044726,"sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","part":{"id":"prt_d78e938f7001tXnBgEr5EuaTBg","messageID":"msg_d78e9238c001JOUfQeSEqnYDyw","sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_25919ace9f3d497ba2ab47fd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n10: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Version display\n13: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n14: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n15: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n18: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n19: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n20: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n21: \n22: ### Requirement: `pack` command\n23: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n26: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n27: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n28: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Successful pack\n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n36: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n37: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `build` command\n41: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n44: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n45: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n46: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n49: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n50: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n51: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Version increment on build\n54: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n55: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n56: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: `publish` command\n59: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n62: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n63: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n66: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n67: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n68: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n71: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n72: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n74: \n75: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n76: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n79: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n80: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Invalid payload\n83: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n84: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n85: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Invalid header format\n88: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n89: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n90: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n93: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n94: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n95: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: `status` command\n98: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n101: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n102: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Not published\n105: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n106: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n107: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n110: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Missing workspace\n113: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n115: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n118: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n119: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n123: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Save location\n126: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n127: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n128: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Schema validation\n131: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n132: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n133: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker integration\n136: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Build image\n139: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n140: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Push image\n144: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n145: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Remove image\n149: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n150: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n154: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Deploy agent\n157: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n158: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n159: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Wait for ready\n162: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n163: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Delete agent\n167: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n168: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Deploy CR\n175: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n176: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n180: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n183: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n184: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n185: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n188: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n191: - **GIVEN** a subcommand’s local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n192: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n193: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand’s `verbose` flag\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: **Note:** The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nCommand-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Global CLI options\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n\n#### Scenario: Version display\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n- **WHEN** the callback runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md","time":{"start":1775850044717,"end":1775850044724}}}}
