{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775850047114,"sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","part":{"id":"prt_d78e94687001yJ6D5irleq2HWb","messageID":"msg_d78e93da40014wJeJBgvXfKNY7","sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775850203678,"sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","part":{"id":"prt_d78e956e8001E2vow07JEWap9N","messageID":"msg_d78e93da40014wJeJBgvXfKNY7","sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","type":"text","text":"Now I have full context. Let me write the focused design.md for AR-020 — CLI pack command.","time":{"start":1775850203676,"end":1775850203676}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850203687,"sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","part":{"id":"prt_d78e9594b001iMhsLGHQ1svB7S","messageID":"msg_d78e93da40014wJeJBgvXfKNY7","sessionID":"ses_287173158ffesFi3rN5hQJtDzn","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_c3b0bcc1f3b74f05993b42f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace for the AgentCube lifecycle. It performs workspace structure validation, merges CLI overrides into agent metadata, optionally generates a language-specific `Dockerfile`, infers missing configuration (entrypoint, agent name), and persists the final `agent_metadata.yaml`. It is the first step in the agent pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke`.\n\n### 1.2 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      CLI (Typer)                              │\n│   kubectl-agentcube pack -f <workspace> [--agent-name ...]    │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │ options dict\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PackRuntime                                │\n│  ┌─────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬────────────┐  │\n│  │ _validate_  │ _load_or_    │ _apply_      │ _validate_ │  │\n│  │ workspace   │ create_meta  │ option_      │ language_  │  │\n│  │ _structure  │              │ overrides    │ compat     │  │\n│  └──────┬──────┴──────┬───────┴──────┬───────┴─────┬──────┘  │\n│         │             │              │             │          │\n│         ▼             ▼              ▼             ▼          │\n│  filesystem check  YAML load    metadata merge   .py/.pom    │\n│                     /create      + defaults      validation  │\n│                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬────────────┐  │\n│  │ _process_   │ _generate_   │ _update_     │ _prepare_  │  │\n│  │ dependencies│ dockerfile   │ pack_meta    │ output_    │  │\n│  │             │              │              │ path       │  │\n│  └──────┬──────┴──────┬───────┴──────┬───────┴─────┬──────┘  │\n│         │             │              │             │          │\n│         ▼             ▼              ▼             ▼          │\n│  pip/maven       Dockerfile     metadata.yaml   output dir   │\n│  scan            template       saved         resolution    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  Rich Progress Spinner                        │\n│  \"✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully!\"                  │\n│  Workspace: /path/to/workspace                                │\n│  Metadata:  /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml            │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Package Layout (pack-relevant modules)\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, PackRuntime export\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, pack() command, _handle_error\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports PackRuntime, MetadataOptions\n│   │   └── pack_runtime.py            — PackRuntime class\n│   └── services/\n│       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n│       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│       └── docker_service.py           — DockerService (used by build, not pack)\n└── examples/\n    ├── hello-agent/main.py            — Example Python agent\n    └── math-agent/main.py             — Example Python agent\n```\n\n### 1.4 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output |\n| `packaging>=23.0` | Language/runtime version detection |\n| `importlib-resources>=6.0.0` | Dockerfile template access |\n| `semver>=3.0.0` | Version handling (indirect, used by build) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 PackRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n    def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n    def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n```\n\n### 2.2 MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n```\n\n### 2.3 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n\n**Validators:**\n- `validate_language` → must be `python` or `java` (lowercased)\n- `validate_build_mode` → must be `local` or `cloud` (lowercased)\n- `validate_port` → must be in range `1..65535`\n\n### 2.4 Sentinel Errors\n\n```python\n# PackRuntime\nValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")\nValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\nValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")\nValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")\nValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")\nRuntimeError(\"Failed to generate Dockerfile: {reason}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 CLI Command Signature\n\n```\nkubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--agent-name` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the agent name |\n| `--language` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language (python, java) |\n| `--entrypoint` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the entrypoint command |\n| `--port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n| `--build-mode` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--output` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for packaged workspace |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### 3.2 Successful Pack Output\n\n```\n✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully!\n  Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n  Metadata:  /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n```\n\n### 3.3 Error Output (verbose=True)\n\n```\nError packaging agent: <error message>\n<full traceback>\n```\n\nExit code: `1`\n\n### 3.4 Error Output (verbose=False)\n\n```\nError packaging agent: <error message>\n```\n\nExit code: `1`\n\n### 3.5 Metadata File Format\n\n**Primary filename:** `agent_metadata.yaml`  \n**Load fallbacks:** `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`\n\n**Save format:**\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\n# ... other fields, None values excluded\n```\n\nWritten with `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)` after `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`.\n\n### 3.6 Workspace Validation Rules\n\n| Language | Requirement | Error if Missing |\n|----------|-------------|------------------|\n| Any | Directory exists | `ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")` |\n| Python | At least one `*.py` file in workspace root | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` |\n| Java | `pom.xml` in workspace root | `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` |\n\n### 3.7 Dockerfile Generation\n\n**When generated:** If no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace root.\n\n**Python Dockerfile template:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM python:3.10-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE {port}\nCMD {entrypoint}\n```\n\n**Java Dockerfile template:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY pom.xml .\nRUN mvn dependency:go-offline\nCOPY src ./src\nRUN mvn package -DskipTests\n\nFROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\nEXPOSE {port}\nCMD {entrypoint}\n```\n\n### 3.8 Entrypoint Inference\n\n| Language | Inference Logic |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Python | Find first `*.py` file in workspace root; default to `python <file>` |\n| Java | Default to `java -jar app.jar` |\n\nIf inference fails and no `--entrypoint` provided: raise `ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")`.\n\n### 3.9 Dependency Processing\n\n| Language | Detection | Action |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| Python | `requirements.txt` exists | Validate file is readable; set `requirements_file` in metadata |\n| Python | `requirements.txt` missing | Create empty file in workspace |\n| Java | `pom.xml` exists | Validate XML is parseable |\n| Java | `pom.xml` missing | Already caught by workspace validation |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Implementation\n\n### 4.1 pack() Entry Point (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"...\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"...\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"...\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"...\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"...\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"...\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"...\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"...\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"...\"),\n) -> None:\n    with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"), transient=True) as progress:\n        task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n        try:\n            runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n            workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n            result = runtime.pack(workspace_path,\n                agent_name=agent_name, language=language, entrypoint=entrypoint,\n                port=port, build_mode=build_mode, description=description, output=output,\n            )\n            progress.update(task, description=\"Done\")\n            console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '[bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]' packaged successfully!\")\n            console.print(f\"  [dim]Workspace:[/dim] {result['workspace_path']}\")\n            console.print(f\"  [dim]Metadata: [/dim] {result['metadata_path']}\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n```\n\n### 4.2 PackRuntime.pack() — Main Orchestration\n\n```python\ndef pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    # 1. Validate workspace structure\n    self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n\n    # 2. Build options dict from CLI args\n    opts = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\n    options_dict = asdict(opts)\n\n    # 3. Load existing metadata or create new\n    metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\n\n    # 4. Apply CLI overrides\n    metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n\n    # 5. Validate language compatibility\n    self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n    # 6. Process dependencies\n    self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n    # 7. Generate Dockerfile if missing\n    dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n    # 8. Update and save metadata\n    self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n\n    # 9. Prepare output path\n    final_workspace = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n\n    return {\n        \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n        \"workspace_path\": str(final_workspace),\n        \"metadata_path\": str(final_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n    }\n```\n\n### 4.3 _validate_workspace_structure\n\n```python\ndef _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    if not workspace_path.exists():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n    if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n```\n\nLanguage-specific checks deferred to `_validate_language_compatibility`.\n\n### 4.4 _load_or_create_metadata\n\n```python\ndef _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n    service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n\n    # Try primary file, then fallbacks\n    primary = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    fallbacks = [workspace_path / \"agent.yaml\", workspace_path / \"metadata.yaml\"]\n\n    if primary.exists():\n        return service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    for fb in fallbacks:\n        if fb.exists():\n            return service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    # Create new metadata from options\n    agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n    return AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=agent_name,\n        language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\") or \"python\",\n        entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\", \"\"),\n        port=options.get(\"port\", 8080) or 8080,\n        build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\") or \"local\",\n        description=options.get(\"description\"),\n    )\n```\n\n### 4.5 _apply_option_overrides\n\n```python\ndef _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n    updates = {}\n    for key in [\"agent_name\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\", \"build_mode\",\n                \"description\", \"region\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\",\n                \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n                \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\"]:\n        value = options.get(key)\n        if value is not None and value != \"\":\n            updates[key] = value\n\n    if updates:\n        service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n        metadata = service.update_metadata(Path(\".\"), updates)  # workspace resolved internally\n\n    # Infer entrypoint if still missing\n    if not metadata.entrypoint:\n        metadata.entrypoint = self._infer_entrypoint(\n            Path(\".\"), metadata.language  # workspace resolved internally\n        )\n\n    return metadata\n```\n\n### 4.6 _validate_language_compatibility\n\n```python\ndef _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n    if metadata.language == \"python\":\n        self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n    elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n        self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n```\n\n### 4.7 _validate_python_compatibility\n\n```python\ndef _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n    if not py_files:\n        raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n```\n\n### 4.8 _validate_java_compatibility\n\n```python\ndef _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n    if not pom.exists():\n        raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")\n```\n\n### 4.9 _process_dependencies\n\n```python\ndef _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n    if metadata.language == \"python\":\n        self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n    elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n        self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n```\n\n### 4.10 _process_python_dependencies\n\n```python\ndef _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    req_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n    if not req_file.exists():\n        req_file.touch()\n```\n\n### 4.11 _process_java_dependencies\n\n```python\ndef _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    # pom.xml already validated; no additional processing needed\n    pass\n```\n\n### 4.12 _generate_dockerfile\n\n```python\ndef _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n    dockerfile = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n    if dockerfile.exists():\n        return dockerfile\n\n    if metadata.language == \"python\":\n        content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n    elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n        content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n    else:\n        return None\n\n    dockerfile.write_text(content)\n    return dockerfile\n```\n\n### 4.13 _generate_python_dockerfile\n\n```python\ndef _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    return f\"\"\"FROM python:3.10-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE {metadata.port}\nCMD {metadata.entrypoint}\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 4.14 _generate_java_dockerfile\n\n```python\ndef _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    return f\"\"\"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY pom.xml .\nRUN mvn dependency:go-offline\nCOPY src ./src\nRUN mvn package -DskipTests\n\nFROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\nEXPOSE {metadata.port}\nCMD {metadata.entrypoint}\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 4.15 _update_pack_metadata\n\n```python\ndef _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n    service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n    service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n```\n\n### 4.16 _prepare_output_path\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n    if output_path:\n        out = Path(output_path).resolve()\n        out.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        return out\n    return workspace_path\n```\n\n### 4.17 _infer_entrypoint\n\n```python\ndef _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n    if language == \"python\":\n        py_files = sorted(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if py_files:\n            return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n        raise ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")\n    elif language == \"java\":\n        return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n    raise ValueError(f\"Cannot infer entrypoint for language: {language}\")\n```\n\n### 4.18 _handle_error (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Configuration\n\n### 5.1 CLI Options → Metadata Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Metadata Field | Override Behavior |\n|------------|----------------|-------------------|\n| `--agent-name` | `agent_name` | Direct override |\n| `--language` | `language` | Direct override, validated against `['python', 'java']` |\n| `--entrypoint` | `entrypoint` | Direct override; if omitted, inferred from workspace |\n| `--port` | `port` | Direct override; default `8080` |\n| `--build-mode` | `build_mode` | Direct override, validated against `['local', 'cloud']` |\n| `--description` | `description` | Direct override |\n| `--output` | — | Controls output directory, not persisted to metadata |\n| `--verbose` | — | Controls logging level and error detail |\n\n### 5.2 Metadata Defaults Cascade\n\n1. **Existing `agent_metadata.yaml`** → loaded values\n2. **Fallback files** (`agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`) → loaded values\n3. **CLI options** → override loaded values (if non-None, non-empty)\n4. **Hardcoded defaults** → fill remaining gaps (`language=python`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=local`)\n5. **Inference** → `entrypoint` derived from workspace files, `agent_name` from directory name\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\n#### PackRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_pack_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPackRuntime_ValidPythonWorkspace` | Valid Python workspace with `main.py` → packs successfully |\n| `TestPackRuntime_ValidJavaWorkspace` | Valid Java workspace with `pom.xml` → packs successfully |\n| `TestPackRuntime_MissingWorkspace` | Non-existent path → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_NoPythonFiles` | Python language, no `*.py` → `ValueError(\"No Python files found\")` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_NoPomXml` | Java language, no `pom.xml` → `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found\")` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_UnsupportedLanguage` | `language=ruby` → `ValueError(\"Unsupported language\")` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_ExistingMetadata` | `agent_metadata.yaml` present → loads and merges |\n| `TestPackRuntime_FallbackMetadata` | Only `agent.yaml` present → loads from fallback |\n| `TestPackRuntime_NoMetadata` | No metadata files → creates new from options |\n| `TestPackRuntime_CliOverrides` | CLI `--agent-name` overrides existing metadata |\n| `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointPython` | No entrypoint, Python workspace → infers `python main.py` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointJava` | No entrypoint, Java workspace → infers `java -jar app.jar` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointFails` | No `*.py` files, no entrypoint → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_GeneratePythonDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Python → generates correct Dockerfile |\n| `TestPackRuntime_GenerateJavaDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Java → generates correct Dockerfile |\n| `TestPackRuntime_ExistingDockerfile` | Dockerfile exists → not regenerated |\n| `TestPackRuntime_CreateRequirementsTxt` | Python workspace without `requirements.txt` → creates empty file |\n| `TestPackRuntime_OutputPath` | `--output` specified → returns output path, not workspace |\n| `TestPackRuntime_MetadataSavedCorrectly` | Metadata file written with correct YAML format |\n| `TestPackRuntime_PortValidation` | `--port=0` → Pydantic validation error |\n| `TestPackRuntime_PortValidationHigh` | `--port=70000` → Pydantic validation error |\n\n#### CLI Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_pack_command.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPackCommand_Success` | `pack -f <valid_workspace>` → success output, exit 0 |\n| `TestPackCommand_Defaults` | `pack` (no options) → uses `workspace=\".\"` |\n| `TestPackCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n| `TestPackCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n| `TestPackCommand_ProgressSpinner` | Runs with Rich Progress spinner visible |\n\n#### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestMetadataService_SaveAndLoad` | Save → load round-trip preserves fields |\n| `TestMetadataService_FallbackLoad` | `agent.yaml` present, `agent_metadata.yaml` absent → loads fallback |\n| `TestMetadataService_ExcludeNone` | `None` fields excluded from YAML output |\n| `TestMetadataService_YamlFormat` | Output uses `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, `default_flow_style=False` |\n\n#### MetadataOptions Tests (`tests/models/test_pack_models.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestMetadataOptions_FromOptions` | `from_options({...})` → correct dataclass fields |\n| `TestMetadataOptions_Defaults` | Empty dict → default values applied |\n| `TestMetadataOptions_PartialOptions` | Partial dict → defaults fill gaps |\n\n### 6.2 Test Helpers\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef python_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef java_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"java-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<project>...</project>\\n\")\n    (ws / \"src\").mkdir()\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_metadata(python_workspace: Path) -> Path:\n    metadata = python_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    metadata.write_text(\"agent_name: test-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nport: 8080\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\")\n    return python_workspace\n```\n\n### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n\n- **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n- **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n- **DockerService:** Not used by pack command; no mocking needed\n- **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n\n### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n5. All PackRuntime public methods have unit tests\n6. Error paths tested (invalid workspace, missing files, bad language)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Deployment Considerations\n\n1. **Workspace Path Resolution:** The `--workspace` path is resolved to absolute via `Path.resolve()` before any operations. Relative paths are supported but normalized.\n\n2. **Metadata File Location:** Always written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`. If the workspace is read-only, pack will fail with a permission error.\n\n3. **Dockerfile Generation:** Only generated if no `Dockerfile` exists. Custom Dockerfiles are preserved. The generated Dockerfile uses fixed base images (`python:3.10-slim`, `maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17`) — users needing different versions must provide their own.\n\n4. **Requirements File:** For Python workspaces without `requirements.txt`, an empty file is created. This ensures the generated Dockerfile's `COPY requirements.txt` step succeeds.\n\n5. **Output Path:** When `--output` is specified, the metadata is still saved to the original workspace, not the output directory. The output path is returned for downstream use (e.g., by a build system that copies the workspace).\n\n6. **Language Validation:** Pydantic validators enforce `language ∈ {python, java}` and `build_mode ∈ {local, cloud}` at the metadata level. CLI-level validation is not performed; errors surface during metadata construction.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Scaffolding (Day 1)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` with `PackRuntime` class skeleton\n2. Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n3. Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options()` classmethod\n4. Write `MetadataOptions` tests\n\n### Phase 2: Core Validation (Day 2)\n\n1. Implement `_validate_workspace_structure`\n2. Implement `_validate_python_compatibility` and `_validate_java_compatibility`\n3. Implement `_validate_language_compatibility` dispatcher\n4. Write validation tests (missing workspace, no Python files, no pom.xml)\n\n### Phase 3: Metadata Handling (Day 3)\n\n1. Implement `_load_or_create_metadata` with fallback logic\n2. Implement `_apply_option_overrides`\n3. Implement `_infer_entrypoint` for Python and Java\n4. Write metadata tests (load, create, override, infer)\n\n### Phase 4: Dockerfile & Dependencies (Day 4)\n\n1. Implement `_process_dependencies`, `_process_python_dependencies`, `_process_java_dependencies`\n2. Implement `_generate_dockerfile`, `_generate_python_dockerfile`, `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n3. Implement `_update_pack_metadata`\n4. Implement `_prepare_output_path`\n5. Write Dockerfile generation tests\n\n### Phase 5: CLI Integration & Polish (Day 5)\n\n1. Implement `pack()` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` with Rich Progress\n2. Wire `_handle_error` for pack command\n3. Implement `pack()` orchestration in `PackRuntime.pack()`\n4. Run full test suite, fix gaps\n5. Run `ruff check`, `mypy`, verify coverage\n\n---\n\n## 9. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | Support for Node.js/Go workspaces | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Custom Dockerfile templates from config | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Multi-stage build optimization for Python (uv/pip-tools) | P3 |\n| AR-0XX | Workspace archive output (tar.gz) for cloud build mode | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Pre-pack hook for custom validation scripts | P3 |\n\n### Known Limitations\n\n- Only `python` and `java` languages are supported; other languages raise an error\n- Dockerfile templates use fixed base image versions; no customization via CLI\n- Entrypoint inference for Python picks the first `*.py` file alphabetically; may not be the correct main file\n- No validation that the inferred entrypoint actually runs successfully\n- Metadata is saved to the original workspace even when `--output` is specified; output directory receives no metadata file\n- No atomicity guarantee: if pack fails midway, partially generated files (Dockerfile, requirements.txt) may remain\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775850